714185f-a.title: Manhattan: 65th Street (West) - Broadway
714185f-a.text:
54 to 34 West 65th Street, south side, eastward between Broadway and
Central Park West, showing a 5-story house, No. 52 being demolished by
the Works Progress Administration. The 9-story building visible is the
Liberty Storage warehouse (Nos. 48-50).

P. L. Sperr.

721131f-b.title: Manhattan: Broadway - Columbus Avenue
721131f-b.text:
The intersection of Broadway and Columbus Avenue, at
Lincoln Square, north from about West 65th Street.
Following the line of Columbus Avenue is the old Ninth
Avenue Elevated Line and which is under demolition at
this date. Broadway is to the left, in the line of
the street car tracks.
October 9, 1940
No's. 1-2-3
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
